### Portfolio endpoints — Makima API
### Base URL: http://localhost:3000

@base_url = http://localhost:3000
# Replace with the JWT returned from register or login.
@access_token = <access_token>
# Replace with a real portfolio UUID.
@portfolio_id = <portfolio_id>

### List portfolios (paginated)
GET {{base_url}}/api/v1/portfolios?page=1&limit=25
Authorization: Bearer {{access_token}}

###

### Create portfolio
POST {{base_url}}/api/v1/portfolios
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{access_token}}

{
  "name": "Fineco Account",
  "description": "My main brokerage account"
}

###

### Create portfolio without description
POST {{base_url}}/api/v1/portfolios
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{access_token}}

{
  "name": "Long-term Bonds"
}

###

### Get portfolio by ID
GET {{base_url}}/api/v1/portfolios/{{portfolio_id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{access_token}}

###

### Get portfolio analytics summary
GET {{base_url}}/api/v1/portfolios/{{portfolio_id}}/summary
Authorization: Bearer {{access_token}}

###

### Update portfolio
PUT {{base_url}}/api/v1/portfolios/{{portfolio_id}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{access_token}}

{
  "name": "Fineco — Equities",
  "description": "Updated description"
}

###

### Update portfolio — clear description
PUT {{base_url}}/api/v1/portfolios/{{portfolio_id}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{access_token}}

{
  "name": "Fineco Account",
  "description": null
}

###

### Delete portfolio
DELETE {{base_url}}/api/v1/portfolios/{{portfolio_id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{access_token}}

###

### Create portfolio with empty name — expect 400
POST {{base_url}}/api/v1/portfolios
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{access_token}}

{
  "name": ""
}
